731189f-a.text:

721505f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 23rd Street
721505f-a.text:
Madison SCuare, looking N.E. from Broadway and 23rd Street, showing
the snow being cleared away. The tower is that of Madison Scquare
Garden (1889-1925). The white marble Appellate Division Supreme
Court building (about 18W6), on the northeast corner of Madison
Avenue and 25th Street, is visible through the trees.
About 1903-1904.
Ewing Galloway, Photographer.

717348f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 23rd Street
717348f-a.text:
Broadway,east side, south across 23rd Street, as photo-
graphed from Fifth Avenue. At the left ia an easterly
view on the south side of East 23rd Street. The corner
structure is the former Hotel Bartholdi. Madison Square
Park is at the left margin and only partially appears.
July 18, 1939
P. L. Sperr

731175f-a.title: Celebrations - Parades - Municipal events - Decoration Day Parade.
731175f-a.text:
Celebrations, Parades and Municipal Events. The Decoration
Day Parade of May 30, 1894 showing the old Guard of the N.G.S.N.Y.
at Madison Square. This photo appears on page 698 of the June 16,
1894 issue of the Illustrated American: Vol. 15.
The photographer is viewing southward on Fifth Avenue from a
point near 25th Street and shows the group, the reviewing stand,
the park and the Hotel Barthold. The latter is at the S.E. corner
of Broadway and E. 23rd Street.
May 30, 1894
The Illustrated American
